Author: Liza Carvelli
Name: Questionable
Description:
A tiny little quest helper plugin, which does quests for you automatically where possible. Uses navmesh to automatically walk to all quest waypoints, and tries to automatically complete all steps along the way (excluding dungeons, single player duties and combat).

Not all quests are supported, check the discord or git repository for an up-to-date list.

Required Plugins: vnavmesh, TextAdvance, Lifestream
Punchline: A tiny quest helper plugin.
Changelog:
v1.22 (2024-07-28)
- Add Heavensward MSQ (until 'Heavensward') thanks to JerryWester
- Add Viper quests
- Pathfinding/following a path via navmesh are no longer considered as 'out of combat' for combat steps (as they can happen to move into cast/melee range)
- Attempt to fix vesper bay aetheryte ticket problems with gate
- Rewrite logic for skipping quest steps to be more flexible

v1.21 (2024-07-28)
- Add last missing quests of Shadowbringers MSQ
- Update targeting logic (primarily relevant melees and/or for overworld enemies)
- Rewrite config + logic for skipping certain quest parts
- Minor updates to tribal quests
- Minor DT aether current updates

v1.20 (2024-07-27)
- Update targeting logic

v1.19 (2024-07-27)
- Add Heavensward MSQ (until 'Heart of Ice'), thanks to JerryWester
- Minor updates to existing tribal quests
- Show version number in quest window
- Always show quest stop button in the same location, even if no quest is active (instead of having it as part of the 'Move to flag'/'Rebuild navmesh' row)
- Update UseItem to check quest work flags for completion + reduce retry/re-check delay
- (dev only) Update quest schema location
- (dev only) Summarize disabled quests per beast tribe instead of listing them individually

v1.18 (testing only) (2024-07-26)
- Adjust targeting logic in combat steps to generally prefer killing quest-related objectives
- Check if you're still within range of your combat target every few seconds
- Use navmesh to move to target if a certain distance away
- Reduce the default cast distance to avoid situations where you're barely out of range
- Stop reusing an item if an item that starts combat leads to you being in combat
- Stop pathfinding/questing if you log out or die
- Updates to Dawntrail quests
- Updates to Ul'dah start quests
- Minor updates to existing daily Pixie/Arkasodara quests
- (dev only) Reorganize ARR files
- (dev only) Fix project file issues

Author: The Combat Reborn Team
Name: Rotation Solver Reborn
Description:
Analyses combat information every frame and finds the best action.

This means almost all the information available in one frame in combat, including the status of all players in the party, the status of any hostile targets, skill cooldowns, the MP and HP of characters, the location of characters, casting status of the hostile target, combo, combat duration, player level, etc.
Then, it will highlight the best action on the hot bar, or help you to click on it.
It is designed for `general combat`, not for savage or ultimate. Use it carefully.
Punchline: Analyses combat information every frame and finds the best action.

Author: daemitus, kawaii
Name: Yes Already
Punchline: Clicks Yes in various dialogs you've specified.
Description: Tired of clicking yes in Praetorium? Can't stand using keys in dungeons? Well do I have the plugin for you! Yes Already is specifically designed to click all the annoying dialogs you've grown accustomed facerolling. Just enter the dialog text, and you'll never see it again! Also works with /regex/ and has several built-in modules for dialogs that aren't quite yes/no prompts but act like it (like desynth).
